oub:footnote.description.oub:description: Declarations are allowed on this code only if the following conditions are fulfilled. Otherwise, another code must be declared. Wines of fresh grapes originating in Morocco and bearing a designation of origin must be accompanied by a certificate indicating their origin or by documents V I 1 or V I 2 annotated in accordance with Article No 50(2) of Commission Regulation (EC) No 555/2008 .(Decision 2003/914/EC - PROTOCOL No 1 on the arrangements applying to imports into the Community of agricultural products originating in Morocco, Article 6 – OJ L345 /2003).

Declarations are allowed on this code only if the following conditions are fulfilled. Otherwise, another code must be declared. Wine with geographical indications originating in Morocco bearing the term “appellation d’origine contrôlée” in accordance with Moroccan law shall be accompanied by a V I 1 or V I 2 document annotated in accordance with the provisions of Article No 25(2) of Commission Regulation (EU) No 2018/273. (Decision 2012/497/EU – PROTOCOL No 1 concerning the arrangements applicable to the importation into the European Union of agricultural products, processed agricultural products, fish and fishery products originating in the Kingdom of Morocco, Article 10 – OJ L241/2012)

oub:certificate.description.oub:description: V I 1 document annotated in compliance with Regulation (EU) 2018/273, Article 25 (2)
V I 2 extract annotated in compliance with Regulation (EU) 2018/273, Article 25 (2)
